\section{Coefficients and thresholds}{

Predictor coefficients report Wald z inference. The estimated category
cut-points render as a subordinate \code{Thresholds} block of rows (they are
intercepts, with SE and p), always on the log-odds scale -- never
exponentiated. Opt out with \code{show_thresholds = FALSE} (compact footer
note instead). Partial-proportional-odds terms render as a
\verb{Non-proportional effects} block, one coefficient per cut-point.
}

\section{Exponentiate and CIs}{

\code{exponentiate = TRUE} yields proportional odds ratios under the logit
link (\code{exp(B)} labels under other links -- never a mislabelled "OR").
\code{ci_method = "profile"} gives profile-likelihood CIs for the predictor
coefficients via \code{confint.polr()} / \code{confint.clm()} (thresholds stay
Wald; a robust \code{vcov} takes precedence); the footer discloses
\verb{95\% CIs: profile likelihood.} when used.
}

\section{Average marginal effects}{

Per-category AME: one column per response category (the marginal effect
on P(Y = k)), the field-standard matrix layout.
}

\section{Robust variance and fit statistics}{

\verb{CR*} via \code{sandwich::vcovCL} for plain proportional-odds fits; refused
(no estimating functions) for \verb{scale = ~} / \verb{nominal = ~} fits. Defaults:
\code{nobs}, McFadden and Nagelkerke pseudo-R-squared (matching Stata \code{ologit}
and SPSS PLUM; closed-form null likelihood), \code{AIC}.
